# XML Master Plan - Token Analyzer Dashboard

```xml
<master_plan>
  <project_name>Token Analyzer Dashboard</project_name>
  <version>1.0</version>
  
  <visual_hierarchy_ui>
    <zone_1>
      <name>Header Section</name>
      <location>Top of dashboard</location>
      <components>
        - Token Symbol: Display prominently (h2, 24px)
        - Token Address: Truncated format (monospace, 12px)
        - Risk Score: Large display (48px, bold, color-coded)
        - Recommendation Badge: BUY/CAUTION/AVOID (button-style, color-coded)
      </components>
      <styling>
        - Background: #ffffff
        - Border: 2px inset #c0c0c0 (Windows 98 style)
        - Layout: Flexbox, space-between alignment
        - Padding: 16px
      </styling>
    </zone_1>
    
    <zone_2>
      <name>Summary Box</name>
      <location>Below header, above three pillars</location>
      <components>
        - Summary Text: Brief 2-3 sentence evaluation
        - Background: #ffffe0 (light yellow, Windows 98 help box style)
        - Border: 2px inset #c0c0c0
      </components>
    </zone_2>
    
    <zone_3>
      <name>AI Summary & Core Evaluation</name>
      <location>Primary content area</location>
      <components>
        - The AI Summary: Generate a dynamic text block evaluating the coin's safety. CRITICAL: You must read @meme-coin-analysis.mdc and use the exact logic and criteria defined there to evaluate the API data and generate this summary.
        - Three Pillars Dashboard: Volume, Narrative, Distribution status cards
        - Each pillar shows: Score (1-10), Status text, Red/Green flags
        - Layout: Grid (3 columns, responsive)
      </components>
      <styling>
        - Section Header: Uppercase, bold, #d4d0c8 background
        - Pillar Cards: White background, 2px inset border
        - Score Display: Large (32px), color-coded (red/yellow/green)
      </styling>
    </zone_3>
    
    <zone_4>
      <name>Detailed Metrics Panels</name>
      <location>Below three pillars</location>
      <components>
        - Liquidity Check: Market cap, liquidity, ratio, status
        - Security Audit: Contract status, dev wallet history, selling activity
        - Social Metrics: X followers, posts per hour, KOL involvement
      </components>
      <styling>
        - Each panel: White background, 2px inset border
        - Metric rows: Label:Value pairs (flexbox, space-between)
        - Status badges: #d4d0c8 background
        - Details text: Italic, smaller font
      </styling>
    </zone_4>
    
    <zone_5>
      <name>Actionable Guidance</name>
      <location>Below metrics panels</location>
      <components>
        - If Buying: Position size, entry strategy, profit targets, stop loss warning
        - If Avoiding: Reason, alternative suggestions
      </components>
      <styling>
        - Panel: White background, 2px inset border
        - Lists: Standard bullet points, 12px font
      </styling>
    </zone_5>
    
    <zone_6>
      <name>Flags Summary</name>
      <location>Below actionable guidance</location>
      <components>
        - Red Flags: List of all red flags (left column, red text)
        - Green Flags: List of all green flags (right column, green text)
      </components>
      <styling>
        - Grid layout: 2 columns, responsive
        - Red flags: Left border 4px solid #c00
        - Green flags: Left border 4px solid #090
        - Font size: 11px
      </styling>
    </zone_6>
  </visual_hierarchy_ui>
  
  <code_standards>
    <react>
      - Use functional components with hooks
      - Extract reusable components (PillarCard, etc.)
      - Use proper prop types or TypeScript if available
      - Keep components focused and single-purpose
    </react>
    <css>
      - Windows 98 aesthetic: #c0c0c0 backgrounds, inset/outset borders
      - Font: 'MS Sans Serif', sans-serif for UI, 'Courier New' for data
      - Color scheme: Classic Windows grays, blues, and system colors
      - Borders: 2px inset/outset for 3D effect
      - No rounded corners (except system defaults)
    </css>
    <data_flow>
      - useTokenData hook fetches and normalizes token data
      - analyzeToken function processes data using three-pillar framework
      - Dashboard component receives analysis object and renders all zones
      - All evaluation logic must reference @meme-coin-analysis.mdc
    </data_flow>
  </code_standards>
  
  <ai_instructions>
    <when_generating_code>
      - Always read @meme-coin-analysis.mdc before writing analysis logic
      - Use the exact evaluation criteria from that file
      - Follow Windows 98 styling guidelines strictly
      - Maintain the zone structure defined in visual_hierarchy_ui
    </when_generating_code>
    <when_generating_summary>
      - CRITICAL: Read @meme-coin-analysis.mdc first
      - Apply the three-pillar framework (Volume, Narrative, Distribution)
      - Use the exact risk scoring methodology defined there
      - Include all red flags and green flags as specified
      - Generate actionable guidance based on the framework's priority order
    </when_generating_summary>
  </ai_instructions>
  
  <api_integration>
    <data_sources>
      - RugCheck API: Distribution and security data
      - Bubblemaps: Holder visualization and bundle detection
      - DexScreener: Volume, liquidity, price data
      - Social APIs: X/Twitter metrics, KOL tracking
    </data_sources>
    <normalization>
      - useTokenData.js hook normalizes all API responses
      - Analyzer functions expect normalized format
      - Handle missing data gracefully (UNKNOWN status, empty flags)
    </normalization>
  </api_integration>
</master_plan>
```

## Key Points

1. **Zone 3 AI Summary**: The instruction explicitly references `@meme-coin-analysis.mdc` and requires reading it before generating summaries.

2. **Visual Hierarchy**: Clear zone structure from header → summary → pillars → metrics → guidance → flags.

3. **Windows 98 Styling**: All CSS follows the classic Windows aesthetic with inset/outset borders and system colors.

4. **Data Flow**: Token data → normalization → analysis → dashboard rendering.

5. **AI Instructions**: Explicitly tells AI to read the meme-coin-analysis.mdc file when generating code or summaries.
